===Etymology===
{{PIE word|en|dwóh₁}}
From {{inh|en|enm|wid}}, {{m|enm|wyd}}, from {{inh|en|ang|wīd||wide, vast, broad, long; distant, far}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*wīdaz}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*h₁weydʰh₁-||to separate, divide}}, a dissimilated univerbation from {{compound|ine-pro|*dwi-|*dʰeh₁-|t1=apart, asunder, in two|t2=to do, put, place|nocat=1}}.

Cognate with {{cog|sco|wyd}}, {{m|sco|wid||of great extent; vast}}, {{cog|fy|wiid||broad; wide}}, {{cog|nl|wijd||wide; large; broad}}, {{cog|de|weit||far; wide; broad}}, {{cog|sv|vid||wide}}, {{cog|is|víður||wide}}, {{cog|la|dīvidō||separate, sunder}}, {{cog|la|vītō||avoid, shun}}. Related to {{l|en|widow}}.

